        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 7:13PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 713 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Venango, or 13 miles southwest of Grant, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grant and Brandon.

This includes Highway 61 between mile markers 68 and 71.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight MDT for
southwestern Nebraska.</instruction>
